gic over the past several days had left the queen exhausted and clearing the undead out so a firewall could be placed had taken its toll.", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "The Queen stood a top the walkway crossing the metal gates of the first wall. The siege had gone on for days. Undead would come but the use of pitch and fire grenades would send them back into the city. But they were running low on these supplies. When they ran out the fight would become an unending melee against the undead that could only be destroyed by fire. "}, "post-37072": {"user": "Raynor of the Celadine", "user_num": 150, "timestamp": "1462829238000", "message": "Luckily the queen was about to get some relief. On the horizon there came a large group of mounted soldiers, and a banner of the Land-Tiller's state. About 300 hundred animals were present, mostly horses and wildebeests, and some rhinos.The troops had the following composition:There were approximately 100 mounted mages and 100 mounted archers. The mages had large staffs from which glowed lights of various colors, creating a sparkling appearance on the horizon. The archers each had two kinds of bows, short and long, for short and long range combat.There were about a dozen earth mages, each accompanied by a powerful earth titan.There were about three dozen psionic corp members, sharing mounts or riding on the earth titans. They were already preparing to cast psionic and defensive spells.There were about 100 falconers, sharing mounts as they channel mana for spells which they would coordinate with their falcons.There were about 50 heavily armed knights on horseback with scale mail for the horses. These were from the Knights of the Harvest.The latest addition to the Land-tiller's forces were the wyvern riders, a mix of mages and archers riding on the backs of small, intelligent wyverns. There were only a handful of these, as they were an experimental force which had not been battle tested. These could be seen soaring above