rior reach due to their altitude and would help snipe the archers from above.The other half of the psionic corps dedicated themselves to defensive spells to help sway the archer vs archer battle more to their side.\u00a0Raynor himself would begin channeling healing and defensive spells to prevent loss of life this early in the battle.The objective wasn't necessarily to kill the undead. Thanks to Ralakor's training and their own past experiences, the Land-Tillers knew that arrows wouldn't be able to kill the undead, but they could at least temporarily cripple them. Shots from 100 lb draw weight bows could penetrate steel armor if necessary, and could send a being made of nothing but bones flying back several meters, causing them to land right on their bare spines, should they connect. Strikes to the limbs could blow the limbs clean off. A good sternum or spine strike could cut an undead in half.Meanwhile, the falcon corps were done charging their mana and were having their falcons place a large number of magical runes on the ground \u00a0and in the air\u00a0behind their own forces as part of their fail safe strategy. The mounted mages and wyvern mages continued to gather power for the Land-Tiller's primary offensive while letting the archers, psionic corps, and Raynor do their work. The undead could expect a nasty surprise as soon as the walls collapsed.The Earth titans started to lumber towards the front line, their casters dismounting them and remaining further back, while the Knights of the Harvest began to flank out towards the sides...", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "Perhaps to Nyx's surprise, the Land-Tillers would immediately rush to the "}, "post-37210": {"user": "Lady Nyx \"The Kingslayer\" Mann", "user_num": 503, "timestamp": "1462911377000", "message": "May 10, 2016 0:24:51 GMT -8 Ralakor Overlord of Belrow said:May 9, 2016 22:19:39 GMT -8 Lady Nyx \"The Kingslayer\" Mann said:They would not have to wait long. Nyx arrived very hastily. She ha